Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: strongSwan fails to start
Symptoms: Service won't start or immediately stops

Solutions:

Check configuration syntax: sudo ipsec checkconfig
Review logs: sudo journalctl -u strongswan -n 50
Verify certificate permissions: ls -la /etc/ipsec.d/private/
Ensure IP forwarding is enabled: sysctl net.ipv4.ip_forward
Issue: Tunnel won't establish
Symptoms: Connection stays in "connecting" state or fails

Solutions:

Verify firewall allows UDP 500, 4500 and ESP protocol
Check certificate validity: sudo ipsec listcerts
Review IKE negotiation logs: sudo ipsec statusall
Ensure both endpoints have correct subnet configurations
Verify time synchronization (certificates are time-sensitive)
Issue: Python scripts fail to execute
Symptoms: Permission denied or module not found errors

Solutions:

Verify script has execute permissions: chmod +x script.py
Check Python path: which python3
Install missing modules: pip3 install <module>
Run with sudo if accessing system commands: sudo python3 script.py
