This lab provided hands-on experience hardening VPN tunnels using strongSwan with modern security practices. Students configured certificate-based authentication, implemented strong cryptographic algorithms with Perfect Forward Secrecy, and created automation scripts for monitoring and recovery. These skills are essential for securing network communications in enterprise environments and protecting data in transit from sophisticated attacks. The combination of proper configuration, strong cryptography, and automated monitoring creates a robust VPN infrastructure suitable for production deployments.

Key takeaways:

Certificate-based authentication provides stronger security than pre-shared keys
Modern cipher suites (AES-256-GCM, SHA-384) protect against current threats
Perfect Forward Secrecy ensures past communications remain secure even if keys are compromised
Automated monitoring and recovery improve VPN reliability and reduce downtime
Defense in depth requires multiple security layers: encryption, authentication, and access control
